You are debugging a production issue where a transaction fails to roll back during an external system outage. A Spring Boot service invokes a local helper method annotated with `@Transactional` to isolate the state changes. However, when an exception is thrown from the helper method, the database changes persist, polluting the database.

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired 
    private PaymentRepository repo;

    public void processPayment(Order order) {
        try {
            executePayment(order);
        } catch (PaymentException e) {
            log.error("Payment failed, retrying...", e);
            throw e;
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void executePayment(Order order) {
        repo.save(order);
        if (externalGatewayFailed()) {
            throw new PaymentException("Gateway Timeout");
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where your microservice orchestrator handles distributed saga steps using `CompletableFuture` chains with a custom thread pool. Under high load, downstream service timeouts trigger exceptions, but instead of executing the compensation logic, the entire service hangs. Heap analysis shows thousands of blocked threads in `ForkJoinPool.commonPool`.

